50|$|Amplification of FGFR1 also {{occurs in}} ~10% of {{estrogen}} receptor positive breast cancers, particularly of the <b>luminol</b> subtype B form of breast cancer. The presence of FGFR1 amplification has been correlated with resistance to hormone blocking therapy {{and found to}} be a poor prognostic factor in the disease.|$|E
